We binarized the coverage values to circumvent the above problem, splitting documents into two classes: informative and uninformative. The binarization method comprised of an absolute and a relative threshold: a document was labeled as informative or {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0039||FO}} if its coverage was greater than {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0040||FO}}, or greater than the coverage of at least {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0041||FO}} of documents for the same {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0042||FO}}; otherwise, it was labeled as uninformative or {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0043||FO}}.